---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Where to Stream the 2026 Global Tournament (Including Free Options)" description="Navigating the broadcast maze: How to watch every single one of the 104 matches.">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4 bg-[#f9a8d4]">
    <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl bg-white border-[4px] border-black p-8 md:p-12 shadow-[12px_12px_0px_#000] relative z-20">
      <div class="inline-block bg-yellow-300 text-black border-[3px] border-black font-black px-4 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">MEDIA & STREAMING</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-6 leading-none" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;">
        Where to Stream the 2026 Global Tournament (Including Free Options)
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-black font-medium leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-black border-l-8 border-l-pink-500">
          Gone are the days when you could just flip on basic cable and watch every match. With 104 games, the broadcasting rights are sliced and diced across networks. Here's how to not get paywalled.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;">1. The Main Providers (USA)</h2>
        <p>
          FOX Sports has the English-language rights, and Telemundo has the Spanish-language rights. If you have a standard cable package or YouTube TV / Hulu + Live TV, you are completely sorted for the big matches. But what about the simultaneous group stage matches?
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;">2. The Tubi Exploit</h2>
        <p>
          Here is the biggest W for broke college students: FOX owns Tubi. In 2022, they dumped full match replays and highlights onto Tubi for completely free. While live matches might still require a cable login via the FOX app, Tubi is your go-to hub if you missed a game because you were stuck in a Zoom meeting.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;">3. Peacock Premium for Spanish Broadcasts</h2>
        <p>
          If you don't care about English commentary (and honestly, Spanish commentary is way more hype anyway), a basic Peacock Premium subscription will give you access to Telemundo's massive slate of games. It is significantly cheaper than buying a whole live TV bundle just for FOX.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-between items-center border-t-[4px] border-black pt-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="font-anton text-xl uppercase text-black hover:text-pink-500 transition-colors">← Back to Guides</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
